---
By: Petrarch
Locus:
  Page: 438
  Verse: 17
Tags:
  - Solitude
---
Solitude is not out to deceive anyone; it does not pretend or embellish; it
has nothing to hide and invents nothing. It is completely naked and without
adornment; it knows nothing of shows or the applause which poisons the
mind. It has God as sole witness of its life and actions.
